<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="vertical-align:baseline"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif">  </span></span></span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Imaging: </span></span></span></span></span>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="vertical-align:baseline"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">AP and lateral plain films; Bilateral oblique films (evaluate for spondylolysis)</span></span></span></span></span></span>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Indications: Pts at risk of fracture, Red flag symptoms, Evaluate for ankylosing spondylitis, No improvement in pain after conservative therapy after 6-12 weeks </span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="vertical-align:baseline"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Non-contrasted MRI (Preferred) </span></span></span></span></span></span>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="line-height:normal"><span style="font-family:Calibri,sans-serif"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:Palatino">Indications: Suspicion for spinal cord/cauda equina compression, Severe neurological deficits, concern for infection, Unexplained inflammatory marker </span></span><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif">↑</span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
